Fetch All Characters¶

Call the API and get all characters.

In [15]:
import requests
import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from collections import defaultdict
from networkx.algorithms.community import girvan_newman

def getAllCharacters():
    url = "https://swapi.info/api/people/"
    res = requests.get(url)
    data = res.json()
    return data

characters = getAllCharacters()
print("Characters fetched:", len(characters))

Characters fetched: 82

Build Character-Film Map¶

Link each character to the films they appear in.

In [16]:
filmToCharacters = defaultdict(set)
characterNames = {}

for person in characters:
    name = person["name"]
    characterNames[name] = person["films"]
    for film in person["films"]:
        filmToCharacters[film].add(name)

Build Coappearance Graph¶

Create edges between characters in the same movie.

In [17]:
graph = nx.Graph()

for film, chars in filmToCharacters.items():
    for c1 in chars:
        for c2 in chars:
            if c1 != c2:
                graph.add_edge(c1, c2)

print("Graph nodes:", graph.number_of_nodes())
print("Graph edges:", graph.number_of_edges())

Graph nodes: 82
Graph edges: 1753

Compute Betweenness Centrality¶

Score how much each character connects others.

In [18]:
bc = nx.betweenness_centrality(graph)
nx.set_node_attributes(graph, bc, "bc")

Detect Communities¶

Use built-in Girvan–Newman to find groups.

In [19]:
communities = next(girvan_newman(graph))
communityMap = {}
for i, group in enumerate(communities):
    for name in group:
        communityMap[name] = i

Draw Graph¶

Color nodes by community. Size by betweenness.

In [20]:
pos = nx.kamada_kawai_layout(graph)
sizes = [5000 * bc[n] for n in graph.nodes()]
colors = [communityMap.get(n, 0) for n in graph.nodes()]

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 12))
nx.draw_networkx_nodes(graph, pos, node_color=colors, node_size=sizes, cmap=plt.cm.tab10, alpha=0.9)
nx.draw_networkx_edges(graph, pos, alpha=0.1, edge_color="gray")

labels = {n: n for n in graph.nodes()}
for node, (x, y) in pos.items():
    plt.text(x, y, node, fontsize=8, ha='center', va='center',
             bbox=dict(facecolor='white', edgecolor='none', alpha=0.6, boxstyle='round,pad=0.2'))

plt.title("Star Wars Character Graph")
plt.axis("off")
plt.savefig("starWarsCharacterGraph.png", bbox_inches='tight', dpi=500)
plt.show()

Filter Top 50 Characters¶

Keep only the 50 most connected characters.

In [21]:
def filterTopNodes(graph, topN=50):
    degreeList = sorted(graph.degree, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    topNodes = [n for n, d in degreeList[:topN]]
    return graph.subgraph(topNodes).copy()

def filterBottomNodes(graph, bottomN=50):
    degreeList = sorted(graph.degree, key=lambda x: x[1])
    bottomNodes = [n for n, d in degreeList[:bottomN]]
    return graph.subgraph(bottomNodes).copy()

filteredGraph = filterTopNodes(graph, topN=50)
print("Top graph has", filteredGraph.number_of_nodes(), "nodes and", filteredGraph.number_of_edges(), "edges")

filteredBottomGraph = filterBottomNodes(graph, bottomN=50)
print("Bottom graph has", filteredBottomGraph.number_of_nodes(), "nodes and", filteredBottomGraph.number_of_edges(), "edges")

pos = nx.spring_layout(filteredGraph, seed=42)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 12))
nx.draw_networkx_nodes(filteredGraph, pos, node_color='gold', node_size=100)
nx.draw_networkx_edges(filteredGraph, pos, alpha=0.3)
for node, (x, y) in pos.items():
    plt.text(x, y, node, fontsize=8, ha='center', va='center',
             bbox=dict(facecolor='white', edgecolor='none', alpha=0.6, boxstyle='round,pad=0.2'))
plt.title("Top 50 Characters by Degree")
plt.axis("off")
plt.savefig("starWarsCharacterGraphTop50.png", bbox_inches='tight', dpi=500)
plt.show()

pos = nx.kamada_kawai_layout(filteredBottomGraph)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 12))
nx.draw_networkx_nodes(filteredBottomGraph, pos, node_color='gold', node_size=100)
nx.draw_networkx_edges(filteredBottomGraph, pos, alpha=0.3)
for node, (x, y) in pos.items():
    plt.text(x, y, node, fontsize=8, ha='center', va='center',
             bbox=dict(facecolor='white', edgecolor='none', alpha=0.6, boxstyle='round,pad=0.2'))
plt.title("Bottom 50 Characters by Degree")
plt.axis("off")
plt.savefig("starWarsCharacterGraphBottom50.png", bbox_inches='tight', dpi=500)
plt.show()
